    "what_description": "Muhlenbergia rigida is a perennial grass species belonging to the family Poaceae. It has a tufted growth habit with erect stems, typically reaching heights of 30-90 cm, and a 3-10 mm wide leaf blade with a glabrous or scabrous texture. The leaf blade has a linear-lanceolate shape, with a flat or slightly inrolled margin, and a glabrous or hairy sheath. Muhlenbergia rigida produces a paniculate inflorescence with a green or purple color, comprising numerous spikelets that are 6-10 mm long and have a 2-3 mm long pedicel. The species is commonly found in dry to moist soils in a variety of habitats, including prairies and rocky outcrops.",
